President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring October 24, 2015, as United Nations Day. In this proclamation, he reflects on the progress made since the establishment of the United Nations 70 years ago and emphasizes the importance of the principles embodied in the UN Charter. He highlights the role of the UN in resolving conflicts, providing humanitarian assistance, and promoting sustainable development. President Obama also acknowledges the challenges that threaten global security and principles and calls for unity and cooperation in meeting these threats. He emphasizes that the idea of the United Nations is based on the notion that people around the world are bound by more than geography and should work together to protect security, environment, health, and human rights. The proclamation encourages the observance of United Nations Day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.